&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT:&lt;/strong&gt; High School Winter Camp&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHEN:&lt;/strong&gt; Friday, January 13 - Sunday, January 15 (students will return in time for 10:45 service on Sunday morning)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHERE:&lt;/strong&gt; Camp Buckner, Burnet, TX&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COST:&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;$175&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High School Winter Camp takes place at Camp Buckner in Burnet, Texas. This weekend camp is one of the highlights of the year for many of our students. It’s a chance for them to take some time away from their routine and encounter God.&nbsp;Students will engage in worship, teaching, and meaningful small groups times. They’ll also spend time just having fun and building relationships with other students.&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://my.hcbc.com/OnlineReg/9176"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;"&gt;REGISTER HERE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A better marriage starts here.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;re|engage&lt;/strong&gt;&nbsp;is a program that offers hope to all marriages – whether you’re struggling to get along, feel more distant than ever before, or simply want to grow closer together as husband and wife. It is a community-driven experience with facilitator couples to help you. It's also a place where you'll be encouraged by the stories of different married couples who have experienced the life change God has brought to their marriages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Spring 2023 semester kicks off on January 31! The semester starts by attending our Open Group Kickoff Sessions on January 31 and February 7 to learn more about re|engage and begin connecting with other married couples. During the kickoff participants will have the opportunity to commit to a Closed Group for the semester. Register below for the Open Group Kickoff and Childcare; registration will be open until January 31.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://my.hcbc.com/OnlineReg/3109?_ga=2.254453192.1329957222.1667829740-654472938.1662558804" target="_blank" class="red-btn" rel="noopener"&gt;REGISTER&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;As more confusion abounds on sexuality and gender, Dr. Christopher Yuan powerfully articulates that God's truth is crystal clear, not gray.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Through the narrative of his personal transformation from an agnostic gay man to a Bible professor, and through his graduate level education in biblical languages, theology, and even health sciences, Dr. Yuan casts a compelling vision of not embracing our sexuality, but embracing Christ, thus shattering the paradigms of gay and straight and pointing us toward the biblical standard of holy sexuality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Dr. Yuan is a highly sought-after expert whose book, &lt;em&gt;Holy Sexuality and the Gospel&lt;/em&gt;, was named 2020 book of the year for social issues by &lt;em&gt;Outreach Magazine.&lt;/em&gt; Christopher will be joined by his mother, Angela, as they minister together testifying to the transformative power of the gospel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="font-weight: 400;"&gt;Save the date February 4 – 5, 2023, for this two-day conference.&nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Registration links and more info coming soon.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

